WEBVTT

00:21.640 --> 00:24.040
♪♪

00:24.240 --> 00:26.040
Cortland: It's not right,

00:26.240 --> 00:27.910
they way she kept you like that.

00:28.110 --> 00:29.050
Deirdre: My daughter's alive.

00:29.240 --> 00:30.870
Lasher's seen her.

00:31.070 --> 00:32.610
Where is he?After all this time,

00:32.810 --> 00:34.140
I still never know.

00:34.340 --> 00:35.920
Rowan: Rowan Fielding,
checking in.

00:36.120 --> 00:38.270
You understand that if
I'm awake now, so is he.

00:38.470 --> 00:39.930
Please, I-I will
explain everything.

00:40.120 --> 00:40.880
I'll be in the lobby
at the Pontchartrain

00:41.080 --> 00:42.930
in five minutes.I'll be there.

00:43.130 --> 00:44.840
You are not keeping me
from my daughter.
[ Grunts ]

00:45.040 --> 00:49.140
♪

00:51.580 --> 00:53.630
[screams]

00:53.830 --> 00:56.640
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:56.840 --> 00:59.540
<i>♪ </i>

01:06.460 --> 01:07.770
[grunting]

01:13.430 --> 01:15.560
[moaning, whimpering]

03:29.000 --> 03:31.580
<i>[dark grungy rock music]</i>

03:31.770 --> 03:35.800
<i>♪ </i>

03:36.000 --> 03:37.700
[elevator chimes]

03:43.190 --> 03:47.230
[no sound]

03:54.680 --> 03:57.380
<i>- So you saw that her neck</i>
<i>was mostly severed,</i>

03:57.580 --> 03:59.510
<i>then you walked toward her</i>
<i>into the elevator?</i>

04:01.200 --> 04:02.730
- I was trying to help.
I'm a doctor.

04:05.860 --> 04:07.520
- And to confirm,
you've never seen

04:07.720 --> 04:10.270
<i>this lady before in your life?</i>

04:10.470 --> 04:12.260
No.

04:14.570 --> 04:16.320
<i>- Okay, Dr. Fielding,</i>
<i>we'll call you</i>

04:16.520 --> 04:18.050
<i>if we need to speak again.</i>

04:24.920 --> 04:27.410
Rowan Fielding?

04:27.610 --> 04:30.280
I'm your great aunt,
Carlotta Mayfair.

04:34.590 --> 04:35.510
Was that my...?

04:35.710 --> 04:37.770
Deirdre Mayfair.

04:37.970 --> 04:39.200
Your mother.

04:41.110 --> 04:44.430
- [clears throat]
Mr. Mayfair is on his way.

04:44.630 --> 04:46.730
- <i>He'd like to speak with you.</i>
- Tell him she's with me.

04:48.250 --> 04:51.660
He would eat you alive.
Come with me.

04:51.850 --> 04:53.530
We'll go to the house.
You'll be safer there.

04:53.730 --> 04:55.350
I have to go.

04:55.550 --> 04:58.440
- What's that, dear?
Go where?

04:58.640 --> 05:01.930
Rowan, I need to speak
with you!

05:02.130 --> 05:03.660
[car horn honks]

05:08.270 --> 05:10.880
[camera shutters clicking]

05:13.060 --> 05:16.550
<i>[eerie music]</i>

05:16.750 --> 05:19.600
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

05:19.800 --> 05:22.120
<i>♪ </i>

05:22.320 --> 05:26.120
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

05:26.320 --> 05:33.040
<i>♪ </i>

05:52.970 --> 05:55.720
- [keypad beeps]
- This is your place?

05:55.920 --> 05:58.240
Yeah.

05:58.440 --> 06:01.720
I know, the security
is a little intense.

06:03.240 --> 06:05.420
I've used it
as a safe house before.

06:25.780 --> 06:29.270
I am so sorry
for the loss of your mother.

06:29.470 --> 06:30.970
I know it must be
such a difficult--

06:31.170 --> 06:33.180
So help me understand this.

06:35.140 --> 06:37.330
- I was gathering information
about you,

06:37.530 --> 06:40.810
your life, your routines,
so I could protect you.

06:41.010 --> 06:43.680
The Talamasca exists
to document and investigate

06:43.880 --> 06:47.550
the, um...unexplained.

06:47.750 --> 06:49.560
And when we see that someone
could be at risk,

06:49.760 --> 06:51.820
we offer protection.

06:52.020 --> 06:53.820
We've been around
since the Middle Ages.

06:54.020 --> 06:57.430
- I mean, not me--
- "Unexplained"?

06:57.630 --> 06:59.990
Seriously? Are you kidding me?

07:01.600 --> 07:04.220
- No.
- Okay.

07:04.420 --> 07:05.780
Whose house is this?

07:07.830 --> 07:10.230
- The Mayfair house
on First Street.

07:10.430 --> 07:12.540
Your aunt lives there.

07:12.730 --> 07:14.890
It goes way back
in your family.

07:15.080 --> 07:16.660
Your mother lived there too.

07:18.230 --> 07:20.660
Who is that?

07:23.060 --> 07:25.330
Please.

07:25.530 --> 07:28.670
There is something, a being.

07:31.550 --> 07:33.900
He used to visit Deirdre.

07:34.100 --> 07:36.820
Ellie was afraid that he might
start to visit you.

07:37.020 --> 07:38.740
<i>Has he?</i>

07:38.930 --> 07:40.480
"Being"? What is that?

07:40.680 --> 07:43.030
What is--
what does that even mean?

07:44.120 --> 07:46.350
We don't really know.

07:46.550 --> 07:47.910
He's connected
with your family.

07:50.350 --> 07:53.270
- They call him Lasher.
<i>- Oh, my God.</i>

07:53.470 --> 07:56.830
I can't believe this shit.
This is crazy.

07:57.700 --> 08:01.930
- Um, you must want
to clean up, take a shower?

08:02.130 --> 08:05.200
And are you hungry?
I'll order some takeout.

08:05.400 --> 08:08.330
[doorbell buzzing]
Um...

08:08.530 --> 08:10.070
I need to go and deal
with something real quick.

08:10.270 --> 08:11.500
Excuse me.

08:13.110 --> 08:15.290
Um...

08:15.490 --> 08:16.950
make yourself at home.

08:17.150 --> 08:18.980
Please, whatever you need.

08:31.560 --> 08:34.660
Before you say anything,
I'm not gonna apologize.

08:34.860 --> 08:36.530
I did what I felt I had to do.

08:36.730 --> 08:38.140
She's here. She's safe.

08:38.340 --> 08:39.620
Fine.

08:39.820 --> 08:41.710
This isn't about
a slap on the wrist.

08:41.910 --> 08:43.230
I'm just here to help.

08:43.430 --> 08:44.980
I've got the team
with me to apply protections

08:45.170 --> 08:47.850
to your place.

08:48.050 --> 08:50.980
But last chance--you sure
you want to keep her here?

08:51.180 --> 08:53.720
- You feel safe?
- I'm good.

08:53.920 --> 08:55.320
She's the one in danger.

08:56.930 --> 08:57.900
Okay.

08:58.100 --> 09:00.820
<i>[soft conspiratorial music]</i>

09:01.020 --> 09:07.770
<i>♪ </i>

09:29.970 --> 09:32.620
<i>[soft ethereal whooshing]</i>

09:36.020 --> 09:37.710
That's a terrible way to die.

09:39.190 --> 09:41.730
I failed her.

09:41.930 --> 09:44.300
I failed our family.

09:44.490 --> 09:47.730
- I failed God.
- No.

09:47.930 --> 09:50.730
You have been
his servant always.

09:53.210 --> 09:55.610
[wind whistling,
branches rattling]

09:55.810 --> 09:57.960
- He's rattling
the trees again,

09:58.160 --> 10:00.180
looking for his whore.

10:00.380 --> 10:02.050
Christ.

10:02.250 --> 10:04.230
30 years,
and he's on to the next one

10:04.430 --> 10:06.620
like it was a minute,

10:06.820 --> 10:08.530
like it was nothing.

10:12.440 --> 10:15.070
What's she like,
Deirdre's daughter?

10:15.260 --> 10:16.670
I...

10:18.800 --> 10:21.290
I think she's made
of sterner stuff

10:21.490 --> 10:22.990
than her mother,

10:23.190 --> 10:26.340
but she needs our protection.

10:26.540 --> 10:28.300
What about a wake?

10:28.500 --> 10:30.250
She'd come to us
if we held her mother's wake

10:30.450 --> 10:32.130
here at the house.

10:32.330 --> 10:34.770
Better she come to us
than Cortland.

10:36.820 --> 10:37.990
A wake?

10:40.170 --> 10:41.080
Yes.

10:42.430 --> 10:44.090
Yes.

10:44.290 --> 10:47.870
- Where's the necklace?
- I took it off Deirdre.

10:51.610 --> 10:53.540
What are you gonna do?

10:53.740 --> 10:55.670
The only thing worth trying.

10:55.870 --> 10:59.460
The only thing
that has ever worked.

10:59.660 --> 11:03.020
Binding him to someone.

11:22.300 --> 11:23.340
[knock on door]

11:27.520 --> 11:29.920
What's with all the gloves?

11:30.120 --> 11:32.130
- What,
a man can't accessorize?

11:33.660 --> 11:37.060
No, it's, um, my gift.

11:37.260 --> 11:39.150
When I touch something
with my hands,

11:39.350 --> 11:43.150
I see its past, some moment
connected to the object.

11:43.350 --> 11:44.980
I can't turn it off.

11:45.180 --> 11:47.160
I wear the gloves
to keep the noise out,

11:47.360 --> 11:49.380
<i>keep from going crazy.</i>

11:49.580 --> 11:51.290
- But at the beach,
you had the gloves on.

11:51.490 --> 11:53.560
It didn't seem
to keep anything out then.

11:53.750 --> 11:55.430
You're an exception.

11:55.630 --> 11:58.820
Your gift is the strongest
thing I've ever felt.

11:59.020 --> 12:01.650
- Do all the Mayfairs
have...gifts?

12:01.850 --> 12:06.660
- Well, from what I've read,
some do, some don't.

12:06.850 --> 12:09.750
Your mother did.
Deirdre, I mean.

12:09.940 --> 12:11.870
- But not Carlotta?
- No.

12:14.610 --> 12:18.800
- At the hotel,
the bellboy said Mr. Mayfair.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.840
- That's Cortland,
your great uncle.

12:22.040 --> 12:23.540
As far as I know,
he doesn't either.

12:23.740 --> 12:26.540
I mean, he has a lot
of the normal kind of power,

12:26.740 --> 12:28.020
wealth-and-influence variety.

12:28.220 --> 12:29.630
<i>He's on the board</i>
<i>of everything.</i>

12:29.830 --> 12:32.120
He owns that hotel
through the Mayfair Trust.

12:32.310 --> 12:35.510
For such a prominent family,
the Mayfairs

12:35.710 --> 12:38.900
are very private people.

12:39.100 --> 12:41.470
I used to walk by that house
on my way to school,

12:41.670 --> 12:45.080
<i>and I always wondered</i>
<i>what went on inside.</i>

12:45.280 --> 12:50.440
I saw something there once that
scared me so much that I ran,

12:50.640 --> 12:54.440
but the next day, there I was,
walking home the same way.

12:54.640 --> 12:58.790
- So you grow up nearby?
Did you know my mom?

12:58.990 --> 13:01.270
Is that why
she had your number?

13:01.470 --> 13:04.450
- No, no, I first spoke to her
when she called

13:04.650 --> 13:07.110
about what happened
with your boss.

13:07.310 --> 13:09.280
She had been in touch with
my predecessor years before

13:09.480 --> 13:10.760
about a playground incident.

13:10.960 --> 13:13.240
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:13.440 --> 13:16.370
- She told me
that that was all in my head...

13:20.150 --> 13:22.430
But she knew it was real.

13:22.630 --> 13:24.210
She knew the whole time.

13:24.410 --> 13:31.520
<i>♪ </i>

13:31.720 --> 13:33.830
I know how you're feeling.

13:34.030 --> 13:36.180
<i>Alone. Ashamed.</i>

13:36.380 --> 13:37.480
Afraid of yourself.

13:37.680 --> 13:39.750
- You have no idea
how I'm feeling.

13:39.950 --> 13:42.100
I felt it when I touched you.

13:42.300 --> 13:43.970
You don't have
to hide that from me.

13:44.170 --> 13:46.280
You have 40 pairs of gloves.

13:46.480 --> 13:48.500
You're the one
who can't handle your shit.

13:48.700 --> 13:50.970
You don't know
anything about me!

13:53.060 --> 13:55.070
I'm sorry.

13:55.270 --> 13:57.460
<i>You're right.</i>

13:57.660 --> 13:59.980
<i>I don't know you.</i>

14:04.890 --> 14:07.210
Um, I have to get back
to the hotel

14:07.410 --> 14:09.870
<i>before any more time passes.</i>

14:10.060 --> 14:12.300
I'll find out who did this.

14:12.500 --> 14:14.570
Don't leave the apartment.

14:14.760 --> 14:17.310
Until we know more, it's not
safe for you out there, okay?

14:17.510 --> 14:19.740
<i>I need your okay on that.</i>

14:21.390 --> 14:22.740
Okay.

14:24.040 --> 14:31.010
<i>♪ </i>

14:38.150 --> 14:41.680
<i>[moody music]</i>

14:41.880 --> 14:48.810
<i>♪ </i>

14:59.510 --> 15:01.350
[window rattling]

15:01.550 --> 15:02.530
[heavy thump]

15:02.730 --> 15:05.570
- [glass cracks]
- Oh! [groans]

15:05.770 --> 15:08.310
<i>[eerie music]</i>

15:08.510 --> 15:14.580
<i>♪ </i>

15:14.780 --> 15:18.190
You're heartbroken, I know.

15:22.360 --> 15:24.060
I loved her too.

15:26.540 --> 15:28.940
But now your time has come.

15:29.140 --> 15:30.850
The 13th witch.

15:34.940 --> 15:37.870
- She's different
from the others,

15:38.070 --> 15:40.780
closed to me somehow.

15:40.980 --> 15:42.520
- I'm sure
you'll find a way in.

15:42.720 --> 15:47.950
<i>♪ </i>

16:06.840 --> 16:09.590
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

16:09.790 --> 16:16.850
<i>♪ </i>

16:24.640 --> 16:27.470
[door clanking]

16:32.000 --> 16:34.310
Who the hell are you?

16:34.510 --> 16:36.970
- I'm a friend of Ciprien's.
Who the hell are you?

16:37.170 --> 16:40.050
- I'm Odette,
Sip's sister.

16:42.050 --> 16:43.710
I'm just here
to grab something.

16:51.890 --> 16:53.500
[murmurs] I knew it.

16:55.200 --> 16:57.030
Well, I'll leave you to it.

16:57.230 --> 16:58.720
Late for my shift.

17:03.770 --> 17:06.910
- Are you seeing my brother?
- No.

17:07.110 --> 17:10.700
No, no, no.
Uh, it's just, um--

17:10.900 --> 17:12.090
it's a work thing.

17:12.290 --> 17:14.660
Ah. Okay.

17:14.860 --> 17:17.180
Hush-hush CIA, FBI shit?

17:17.380 --> 17:19.750
Oh, I'll never tell.

17:19.950 --> 17:22.840
When are you due?

17:23.040 --> 17:24.840
A couple of weeks.

17:25.040 --> 17:27.760
- Congratulations.
- Oh, it's not mine.

17:27.960 --> 17:29.460
Um, I'm a surrogate.

17:29.660 --> 17:30.940
Yeah, this little girl
is going to a couple

17:31.130 --> 17:34.290
of nice daddies uptown.

17:34.490 --> 17:38.770
- Have you done that before?
- First time.

17:38.970 --> 17:42.950
- Do you feel connected to her?
- Not really.

17:43.150 --> 17:44.510
I feel connected
to the heartburn,

17:44.710 --> 17:46.470
that's for sure.

17:46.670 --> 17:49.040
I bet she does, though.

17:49.240 --> 17:50.740
I'm sorry?

17:50.940 --> 17:53.650
- I bet she feels connected
to you.

17:53.850 --> 17:55.660
She'll wonder about you
her whole life

17:55.860 --> 17:57.570
and dream about you.

17:57.770 --> 18:01.100
[smoke alarm blaring]

18:01.300 --> 18:08.220
<i>♪ </i>

18:13.060 --> 18:15.330
This could be hours.

18:15.530 --> 18:17.890
I have to get to work, so...

18:18.970 --> 18:20.810
Yeah, no worries.

18:21.010 --> 18:22.990
I have an aunt that lives
nearby here, I think.

18:23.190 --> 18:24.470
Which way is First Street?

18:24.670 --> 18:26.950
- Like, a 10-minute walk
that way.

18:27.150 --> 18:30.170
- Just straight down?
- Yeah, yeah, you'll find it.

18:30.370 --> 18:33.560
- Okay. Thank you.
- Bye.

18:33.760 --> 18:39.700
<i>♪ </i>

18:39.900 --> 18:42.910
[sirens wailing]

18:52.050 --> 18:54.850
<i>40 years.</i>

18:55.040 --> 18:57.590
- 42 plus some.
<i>- Mm.</i>

18:57.790 --> 19:01.370
You were still married
when you came to this house.

19:01.570 --> 19:03.550
He was no good for you.

19:03.750 --> 19:05.190
I remember that much.

19:07.760 --> 19:09.820
Do you remember
when she was a little girl,

19:10.020 --> 19:13.170
how you'd sing her to sleep?

19:13.370 --> 19:16.260
Yes, ma'am, of course I do.

19:16.460 --> 19:20.080
- There was a time she
wouldn't have anyone but you.

19:24.780 --> 19:26.220
Mm.

19:29.780 --> 19:31.870
She left you this.

19:35.360 --> 19:38.980
- Put it on.
- Oh, no, I couldn't.

19:39.180 --> 19:42.630
- It's an heirloom.
- Put it on.

19:42.830 --> 19:45.420
She was so attached to it.

19:45.620 --> 19:47.540
- That must be why
she left it to you.

20:05.080 --> 20:06.260
Thank you.

20:09.950 --> 20:11.100
Now, come.

20:11.290 --> 20:13.350
I need your help
with something.

20:24.750 --> 20:27.280
- Was it the damask or
shantung curtains you wanted?

20:29.190 --> 20:32.120
Oh, Delphine.

20:32.320 --> 20:34.250
I left you in charge of her.

20:34.450 --> 20:36.250
[deep rumbling]

20:36.450 --> 20:38.950
[eerie growling]

20:39.150 --> 20:41.470
May God forgive you.

20:41.670 --> 20:44.520
<i>[eerie music]</i>

20:44.720 --> 20:51.130
<i>♪ </i>

20:53.080 --> 20:55.960
- Oh, no.
[sobs softly]

20:59.870 --> 21:03.400
[insects chirping]

21:12.500 --> 21:15.330
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

21:15.530 --> 21:22.510
<i>♪ </i>

21:22.710 --> 21:24.990
- What's up?
You lost?

21:26.640 --> 21:28.130
Hey. Where you going?

21:28.330 --> 21:29.040
- [laughs]
- Over here, baby.

21:29.240 --> 21:30.300
Come back.

21:37.480 --> 21:40.970
<i>singer:</i>
<i>♪ We are the Northside </i>

21:41.170 --> 21:43.100
[upbeat percussive music]

21:43.300 --> 21:45.800
<i>♪ We stomp to rise you </i>

21:46.000 --> 21:48.670
<i>♪ Before you die </i>

21:48.870 --> 21:51.330
<i>♪ You scared of death,</i>
<i>though ♪</i>

21:51.530 --> 21:54.290
<i>♪ You'll ride together </i>

21:54.490 --> 21:57.200
<i>♪ Next time you see us </i>

21:57.400 --> 22:00.160
<i>♪ Be too late to cry </i>

22:00.360 --> 22:02.770
[continuing indistinctly]

22:02.970 --> 22:09.680
♪

22:32.270 --> 22:33.920
How did you know him?

22:35.970 --> 22:38.760
- I'm crying
for somebody else tonight.

22:38.960 --> 22:40.160
I'm sorry.

22:40.360 --> 22:41.410
I lost someone too.

22:44.200 --> 22:46.120
We'll meet again.

22:46.320 --> 22:48.470
He's still here.

22:48.670 --> 22:50.460
They all are,
if you know where to look.

22:52.160 --> 22:54.040
No one is ever gone.

22:54.240 --> 22:55.820
Only separated for a minute.

22:57.430 --> 23:00.610
- It must be nice
to see it that way.

23:00.810 --> 23:03.090
It is.

23:03.290 --> 23:06.400
You can too. This will help.

23:06.600 --> 23:08.230
- Oh, no, I'm okay.
Thank you.

23:08.430 --> 23:10.190
One for my friend here.

23:10.390 --> 23:11.480
That one.

23:13.010 --> 23:15.410
- I--no, uh, thank you.
- It's paid for.

23:15.610 --> 23:16.450
Take it.

23:23.630 --> 23:27.770
<i>[eerie bass whooshing]</i>

23:27.970 --> 23:30.330
Have a nice night.

23:31.590 --> 23:32.950
Well?

23:33.150 --> 23:34.210
Well what?

23:34.410 --> 23:36.130
Now we dance.

23:36.330 --> 23:39.780
- Oh, no, I--
- It's not for you.

23:39.980 --> 23:41.000
It's for them.

23:41.200 --> 23:42.870
But I have to go.

23:43.070 --> 23:45.050
Now we dance.

23:45.250 --> 23:50.880
<i>♪ </i>

23:51.080 --> 23:52.750
[zipper sound]

23:52.950 --> 23:55.580
- Don says the security feed
is working fine now, sir.

23:55.780 --> 23:58.500
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

23:58.700 --> 24:00.540
<i>♪ </i>

24:00.740 --> 24:02.980
<i>The system's been</i>
<i>operating perfectly.</i>

24:03.180 --> 24:04.890
<i>I don't know what could've</i>
<i>caused that kind of gap</i>

24:05.090 --> 24:06.460
<i>in the footage.</i>

24:06.660 --> 24:13.590
<i>♪ </i>

24:22.420 --> 24:24.690
- Evening.
<i>- Bonswa.</i>

24:25.210 --> 24:26.050
Uh...

24:26.250 --> 24:29.260
[speaking Creole]

24:33.260 --> 24:34.350
[speaking Creole]

24:37.000 --> 24:37.840
<i>Merci.</i>

24:38.040 --> 24:44.930
<i>♪ </i>

24:52.240 --> 24:56.410
[high-pitched humming]

24:58.240 --> 25:00.510
[high-pitched humming]

25:06.250 --> 25:10.430
[high-pitched humming]

25:14.870 --> 25:17.750
[upbeat percussive music]

25:17.950 --> 25:24.230
♪

25:44.590 --> 25:47.870
[percussive music continues]

25:48.070 --> 25:54.820
♪

26:01.220 --> 26:02.610
- Hi.
- Hi.

26:04.920 --> 26:07.790
- That's an interesting mask.
- Thank you.

26:09.750 --> 26:11.050
Do you wear masks?

26:12.880 --> 26:13.940
No.

26:14.140 --> 26:15.060
<i>No?</i>

26:17.320 --> 26:19.060
No, why would you?

26:21.540 --> 26:22.850
What's your name?

26:24.330 --> 26:25.850
Adonis.

26:27.680 --> 26:30.260
That's your real name?

26:30.460 --> 26:32.160
It's my name tonight.

26:33.560 --> 26:34.390
Okay.

26:34.590 --> 26:41.270
<i>♪ </i>

26:41.470 --> 26:42.650
San Francisco.

26:46.130 --> 26:48.180
I'm sorry, I thought
you asked where I was from.

26:50.010 --> 26:52.060
See, I was just about to.

26:52.260 --> 26:53.880
You read my mind.

26:57.450 --> 27:00.500
Be careful what you think.

27:00.700 --> 27:02.420
- Oh, I don't like
to be careful.

27:02.620 --> 27:09.550
<i>♪ </i>

27:30.610 --> 27:31.790
Don't be afraid.

27:37.270 --> 27:40.360
The dead are with us always.

27:47.240 --> 27:50.080
[jaunty, haunting tune]

27:50.280 --> 27:56.260
♪

27:56.460 --> 27:57.810
You remind me of her.

28:01.080 --> 28:02.700
You know you're special,
don't you?

28:02.900 --> 28:09.830
<i>♪ </i>

28:18.230 --> 28:20.620
You're exactly where
you're meant to be right now.

28:22.060 --> 28:23.060
Can you feel it?

28:25.670 --> 28:26.720
Yes.

28:26.920 --> 28:33.590
<i>♪ </i>

28:42.680 --> 28:46.210
[crowd noise, moody music]

28:52.430 --> 28:54.780
[neon buzzing]

29:01.570 --> 29:03.630
- You get used to it.
[light laugh]

29:03.830 --> 29:06.720
Although this is
some crazy first-day shit.

29:06.920 --> 29:08.230
Deirdre Mayfair.

29:09.670 --> 29:11.770
[camera shutter clicking]

29:11.970 --> 29:12.940
- What was wrong
with the photos

29:13.140 --> 29:14.900
the girl took before?

29:15.100 --> 29:16.990
- They were a little blurry.
[lens snaps]

29:17.190 --> 29:19.240
- Typical.
[chuckles]

29:21.200 --> 29:24.000
<i>You just started</i>
<i>the forensics rotation?</i>

29:24.200 --> 29:25.260
Yeah.

29:25.460 --> 29:27.130
- Don't y'all usually
rotate at once?

29:27.330 --> 29:29.910
I feel like I usually see
all the newbs at the same time.

29:30.110 --> 29:33.690
- It's just me.
Do you have her clothes?

29:35.820 --> 29:38.010
- [chuckles]
They're in evidence, man.

29:38.210 --> 29:41.010
- It's a murder investigation.
- Right.

29:41.210 --> 29:42.620
And you better hurry up too.

29:42.820 --> 29:45.020
Lonigan's picking her up
for embalming, like, stat.

29:45.220 --> 29:47.150
- That's a quick turnaround.
<i>- Yeah, well,</i>

29:47.350 --> 29:49.060
the rules don't apply
when you're a Mayfair.

29:49.260 --> 29:51.680
<i>They want fast, they get fast.</i>

29:51.870 --> 29:54.940
Screw waiting in line
like the rest of us.

29:55.140 --> 29:56.670
Sounds nice, right?

30:20.220 --> 30:22.840
No! No!

30:23.040 --> 30:25.840
Bring her back! No!
[screaming]

30:26.040 --> 30:28.100
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

30:28.300 --> 30:29.890
Please!

30:30.090 --> 30:37.320
<i>♪ </i>

30:59.730 --> 31:02.620
[upbeat percussive music]

31:02.820 --> 31:09.740
♪

31:31.290 --> 31:32.470
Wait!

31:32.670 --> 31:35.520
<i>[eerie music]</i>

31:35.720 --> 31:42.780
<i>♪ </i>

32:03.670 --> 32:05.150
You're dead.

32:06.890 --> 32:09.330
I held your body.

32:09.530 --> 32:11.990
[owl hoots]

32:12.190 --> 32:13.630
Am I dead?

32:15.110 --> 32:16.070
No.

32:17.460 --> 32:19.950
You're very much alive.

32:20.150 --> 32:22.000
You're perfect.

32:22.200 --> 32:24.870
It's just how
I imagined you'd be.

32:25.070 --> 32:27.000
Oh, my little girl.

32:31.780 --> 32:35.620
- This can't be happening.
- But it is.

32:35.820 --> 32:37.090
You know it is.

32:38.920 --> 32:40.750
They told me you were dead.

32:42.320 --> 32:44.750
I would never,
never give you up.

32:46.540 --> 32:48.680
You're not dead.

32:48.880 --> 32:50.420
You're not dreaming.

32:50.620 --> 32:53.070
You're awake,

32:53.270 --> 32:57.030
and you're just beginning to
see the world behind the world.

32:58.770 --> 33:00.250
Isn't it beautiful?

33:01.940 --> 33:04.220
You can have this all the time.

33:04.420 --> 33:08.120
If you open your mind,
you can be transformed.

33:09.780 --> 33:11.830
- I don't want
to be transformed.

33:12.030 --> 33:14.440
I just want to be me.

33:14.640 --> 33:18.920
- But you aren't that yet,
not without us.

33:20.180 --> 33:21.920
You've felt alone, haven't you?

33:24.400 --> 33:26.760
Because you're disconnected.

33:26.960 --> 33:29.240
From your blood,

33:29.440 --> 33:31.030
from me,

33:31.220 --> 33:33.380
your grandmother,
your great-grandmother,

33:33.570 --> 33:35.720
on back to the beginning.

33:37.980 --> 33:40.250
This is where we are connected.

33:40.450 --> 33:42.900
This is where
we find each other.

33:44.640 --> 33:46.690
Through him.

33:46.890 --> 33:49.390
<i>[dark music]</i>

33:49.590 --> 33:54.270
<i>♪ </i>

33:54.470 --> 33:55.960
You're not her.

33:56.160 --> 33:58.740
<i>[voices whispering</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

34:05.090 --> 34:08.280
Miss, you need some help?

34:08.480 --> 34:10.720
Are you okay?

34:10.920 --> 34:13.930
[indistinct chatter]

34:15.670 --> 34:18.420
- Yeah?
- Sorry. Yeah.

34:18.620 --> 34:19.500
All right.

34:32.210 --> 34:34.440
- Did you get
the drawing I sent?

34:34.640 --> 34:38.180
<i>- Yep, that's him?</i>
- Uh-huh, I saw it.

34:38.380 --> 34:40.660
He stopped the elevator
and got in with her.

34:40.860 --> 34:42.790
<i>And then?</i>

34:42.990 --> 34:45.010
That's all I saw.

34:45.210 --> 34:47.750
<i>- That's great, that's plenty.</i>
<i>I'll send it around.</i>

34:47.950 --> 34:50.100
- <i>We'll get him.</i>
- Yes, we will.

34:51.490 --> 34:52.580
Wait!

34:54.930 --> 34:56.760
I wanted to give you this.

34:56.960 --> 34:58.550
It's next week. It's a rally.

34:58.750 --> 35:01.900
- What for?
- Brotherhood.

35:02.100 --> 35:03.900
I know you're not
a medical student, man.

35:04.100 --> 35:05.600
Come on.

35:05.800 --> 35:08.770
You heard the rumors
about the family.

35:08.970 --> 35:10.470
You came here
to see for yourself.

35:10.670 --> 35:12.690
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

35:12.890 --> 35:15.560
She's a witch.

35:15.760 --> 35:19.480
You just touched the body
of a real goddamn witch.

35:19.680 --> 35:21.570
A witch?

35:21.770 --> 35:23.140
Come on.

35:23.340 --> 35:27.490
[chuckles]
Listen to yourself, man.

35:27.690 --> 35:29.050
There's no such thing.

35:33.920 --> 35:35.890
My mistake.

35:36.090 --> 35:38.940
[sirens blaring]

35:39.130 --> 35:46.060
<i>♪ </i>

36:01.910 --> 36:03.180
[buzzing]

36:03.380 --> 36:06.430
[fire crackling]

36:09.610 --> 36:11.050
Rowan.

36:12.310 --> 36:14.270
Are you okay?

36:15.350 --> 36:16.440
I don't know.

36:18.050 --> 36:19.100
I think so.

36:21.710 --> 36:23.410
Let's get you inside.

36:33.150 --> 36:36.110
<i>[muffled thudding]</i>

36:40.210 --> 36:43.520
- He doesn't like her
wearing it.

36:43.720 --> 36:46.830
<i>- If it traps him down there</i>
<i>with her, it'll be worth it.</i>

36:47.030 --> 36:48.470
<i>[thudding continues]</i>

37:07.750 --> 37:10.510
- I have no doubt that
all three of them were him.

37:10.700 --> 37:13.330
He can take different forms.

37:13.530 --> 37:16.370
- I really miss
the world making sense.

37:17.070 --> 37:19.340
It never made sense.

37:19.540 --> 37:21.260
Most people
just can't see that.

37:21.450 --> 37:23.510
So what'd you find out?

37:26.340 --> 37:28.000
- First, I found out
that someone doesn't want me

37:28.200 --> 37:30.350
to find anything out.

37:30.550 --> 37:32.430
Elevator's been
wiped of memories.

37:33.130 --> 37:35.920
I touched the walls,
and I got nothing.

37:36.120 --> 37:38.580
That's never happened before.

37:38.780 --> 37:40.930
But then I went to the morgue,
I touched the body,

37:41.130 --> 37:42.970
and I saw a guy stop
the elevator

37:43.170 --> 37:44.710
and get in with her.

37:44.910 --> 37:46.500
I sent his likeness
to the team.

37:46.700 --> 37:48.320
They're out looking for him.

37:50.100 --> 37:51.550
Whatever else Lasher can do,

37:51.750 --> 37:54.940
I see he has the power
to dehydrate you.

37:55.140 --> 37:56.320
Yeah, Jesus.

37:59.370 --> 38:00.940
So you touched the body?

38:11.730 --> 38:14.310
I saw your birth.

38:14.510 --> 38:17.220
She didn't give you away.

38:17.420 --> 38:18.960
You were taken from her.

38:19.160 --> 38:21.010
<i>[solemn music]</i>

38:21.210 --> 38:22.960
I felt her heart break.

38:24.960 --> 38:28.240
It was the strongest memory
left in that body.

38:28.430 --> 38:30.010
She loved you.

38:32.710 --> 38:34.760
- Yeah, she said that, too,
but it was just him

38:34.960 --> 38:37.770
telling me
whatever I wanted to hear.

38:37.970 --> 38:39.450
It was all lies.

38:40.890 --> 38:42.590
Not that part.

38:45.770 --> 38:47.950
- Do you think
it was the drink?

38:48.150 --> 38:51.130
Or can he just get
in my head whenever he wants?

38:51.330 --> 38:52.910
I don't know.

38:53.110 --> 38:55.780
I do know
he can't get to you in here.

38:55.980 --> 38:57.830
He lit that fire to get you
out of the apartment.

38:58.030 --> 39:00.570
I saw that much.

39:00.770 --> 39:02.790
- I didn't even
feel it starting.

39:02.990 --> 39:04.750
I was just in it.

39:04.950 --> 39:07.010
Like, I just felt
like I was swept away.

39:07.210 --> 39:09.800
And I don't
know how to stop it.

39:10.000 --> 39:12.800
I mean,
if that's how this works,

39:13.000 --> 39:14.590
how he works.

39:14.790 --> 39:16.200
- Well, that's why
you need to understand

39:16.400 --> 39:20.240
the full extent of your power
so you can defend yourself.

39:20.440 --> 39:21.810
I can help you with that.

39:22.010 --> 39:24.030
I can go into those moments,
slow things down

39:24.230 --> 39:27.820
so we can see how it works,
what's really happening.

39:28.020 --> 39:30.820
You mean touch me again?

39:31.020 --> 39:32.950
You're not afraid
I'll hurt you?

39:33.150 --> 39:35.080
No.

39:35.280 --> 39:37.160
Last time, I was a stranger.

39:39.430 --> 39:42.600
Now I think
you trust me a little.

39:45.040 --> 39:47.300
Maybe a little.

39:49.740 --> 39:55.020
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

39:55.220 --> 39:56.530
Let's do it.

39:59.060 --> 40:01.850
- I'm ready.
- Okay.

40:02.050 --> 40:08.670
<i>♪ </i>

40:34.090 --> 40:36.010
[energy humming]

40:36.210 --> 40:38.230
[inhales sharply]

40:38.430 --> 40:41.020
<i>[rhythmic electronic music]</i>

40:41.220 --> 40:47.710
<i>♪ </i>

41:02.380 --> 41:05.960
♪

41:06.160 --> 41:09.700
No wonder everyone's looking
at me like I'm a ghost.

41:09.900 --> 41:11.750
Woman:
The Mayfair matriarchs,

41:11.950 --> 41:15.490
300 years of women handing down
everything to their daughters.

41:15.690 --> 41:17.270
How many families
can say that?

41:17.470 --> 41:18.970
[Wind whistles]

41:19.170 --> 41:21.930
He's coming for her.

41:22.130 --> 41:22.890
What even is he?

41:23.090 --> 41:25.930
Ask him.

41:26.130 --> 41:27.280
[Gasps]

41:27.480 --> 41:30.500
♪

41:31.930 --> 41:40.170
♪

41:40.370 --> 41:42.380
[Elevator dings]

41:44.990 --> 41:48.900
Rowan in that elevator
is in shock and trauma.

41:50.250 --> 41:52.790
The camerawork, the beautiful
cinematography is meant

41:52.990 --> 41:54.920
to suggest the state
that Rowan's in,

41:55.120 --> 41:56.920
the way in which
she's not really tracking

41:57.120 --> 41:58.230
what's happening.

41:58.430 --> 42:00.580
But she does see this face
that she will come to know,

42:00.780 --> 42:02.930
that's the face
of her Aunt Carlotta.

42:03.130 --> 42:05.450
♪

42:05.650 --> 42:08.020
Rowan Fielding,
I'm your great-aunt

42:08.220 --> 42:09.720
Carlotta Mayfair.

42:09.920 --> 42:13.760
Is that my --Deirdre Mayfair, your mother.

42:13.960 --> 42:16.160
Rowan is in such
a state of shock and trauma

42:16.360 --> 42:18.070
she does not know who to trust.

42:18.270 --> 42:20.290
Mr. Mayfair's on his way,
he'd like to speak with you.

42:20.490 --> 42:22.760
Tell him she's with me.

42:23.770 --> 42:25.730
He would eat you alive.

42:25.930 --> 42:28.910
Esta: She sees Cip,
and this is the person

42:29.110 --> 42:30.610
who has said to her, "I can tell
you who you are.

42:30.810 --> 42:31.960
I can help you understand."

42:32.160 --> 42:33.390
I have to go.

42:33.590 --> 42:35.400
What's that, dear?

42:35.590 --> 42:37.660
So that is who she trusts
in this moment

42:37.860 --> 42:39.610
and who she goes to.
[Car horn honks]

42:41.130 --> 42:43.010
I was gathering information
about you,

42:43.210 --> 42:46.930
your life, your routine
so I could protect you.

42:47.130 --> 42:49.710
The Talamasca exists
to document and investigate

42:49.910 --> 42:53.280
the, um, unexplained.

42:53.480 --> 42:54.500
Unexplained?

42:54.700 --> 42:56.150
Seriously?

42:56.350 --> 42:58.060
Are you kidding me?

42:58.710 --> 43:01.460
No.She is a scientist.

43:01.660 --> 43:04.950
All of those years of training
have not allowed her

43:05.150 --> 43:08.210
to believe in anything like
what Ciprien's telling her.

43:08.410 --> 43:13.080
Something -- a being,
he used to visit Dierdre.

43:13.280 --> 43:15.520
Ellie was afraid that he might
start to visit you.

43:15.720 --> 43:17.440
She just cannot believe it.

43:17.640 --> 43:18.610
"Being"?

43:18.810 --> 43:20.050
What is that?
What it's --

43:20.250 --> 43:21.350
What does that even mean?

43:21.550 --> 43:23.660
We don't really know.

43:23.860 --> 43:24.840
He's connected
with your family.

43:25.040 --> 43:27.930
I think that Cip understands
more than anyone

43:28.130 --> 43:31.280
what a potent and powerful,
magical being Rowan is,

43:31.480 --> 43:33.280
and he needs to help her
sort through that.

43:33.480 --> 43:35.620
[Door opens, shuts]

43:38.270 --> 43:41.070
Both Lasher and Rowan are
grieving Dierdre,

43:41.270 --> 43:43.510
and are going
through this kind of grieving

43:43.710 --> 43:45.510
and funeral process together.

43:45.710 --> 43:48.690
They meet in the midst
of this second line parade.

43:48.890 --> 43:51.300
And the way he finds
to connect with her

43:51.500 --> 43:54.560
is through this mutual
experience of grief

43:54.760 --> 43:56.740
that brings them together
in the second line,

43:56.940 --> 43:59.350
and then, you know,
this magical concoction

43:59.550 --> 44:03.310
that he gives her that makes her
sort of open herself up

44:03.510 --> 44:04.690
in some ways.

44:11.610 --> 44:12.800
You remind me of her.

44:13.000 --> 44:16.060
♪

44:16.260 --> 44:21.370
You know you're special,
don't you?

44:21.570 --> 44:23.850
And then, of course,
the last way that he uses

44:24.050 --> 44:25.680
to try to open
and connect with her is

44:25.880 --> 44:27.640
he embodies the form of Dierdre.

44:27.840 --> 44:29.760
My little girl.

44:33.550 --> 44:36.250
This can't be happening.

44:36.450 --> 44:37.470
But it is.

44:37.670 --> 44:40.300
But Rowan, even in that moment,
is so guarded.

44:40.500 --> 44:42.300
You're not her.

44:42.500 --> 44:44.520
She's onto it.
She knows that it is Lasher

44:44.720 --> 44:45.950
trying to manipulate her.

44:49.080 --> 44:51.480
Miss, do you need
some help?

44:53.260 --> 44:55.050
Are you okay?

44:58.920 --> 45:00.760
I didn't even feel it
starting.

45:00.960 --> 45:02.540
I was just in it.

45:02.740 --> 45:04.670
Like, I just felt like
I was swept away.

45:04.870 --> 45:06.850
And I don't know
how to stop it.

45:07.050 --> 45:08.980
That's why you need to
understand the full extent

45:09.180 --> 45:12.160
of your powers
so you can defend yourself.

45:12.360 --> 45:13.900
I can help you
with that.

45:14.100 --> 45:16.020
You mean touch me again?

45:16.980 --> 45:18.510
You're not afraid
I'll hurt you?

45:18.710 --> 45:20.780
No.

45:20.980 --> 45:22.640
Last time,
I was a stranger.

45:24.250 --> 45:27.440
And, well, I think you
trust me a little.

45:27.640 --> 45:31.140
Incredibly deep, really,
for Rowan in this moment

45:31.340 --> 45:33.400
with Cip,
that she has decided

45:33.600 --> 45:34.660
to trust someone.

45:34.860 --> 45:35.790
Let's do it.

45:35.990 --> 45:39.190
Decided to put aside
her rational mind

45:39.390 --> 45:43.010
for a moment and open up to what
might really be going on.

45:44.840 --> 45:48.410
This felt like the first time
we really get to see Rowan

45:48.610 --> 45:52.320
let down her guard and relax
and connect with someone.

45:54.370 --> 45:58.120
In some ways, this is more
profound than seeing a sex scene

45:58.320 --> 45:59.640
between these two characters.

45:59.840 --> 46:03.780
It's more profound for someone
as guarded as Rowan

46:03.980 --> 46:06.650
to open up herself
to someone else,

46:06.850 --> 46:10.000
knowing all of her memories,
all of her past,

46:10.200 --> 46:14.480
and asking that person
to help her understand

46:14.680 --> 46:17.920
this new force within herself
that she has no idea about.

46:18.120 --> 46:30.270
♪

46:33.930 --> 46:36.590
<i>♪ We are the Northside </i>

46:36.790 --> 46:39.460
<i>♪ The Skull and Bones Gang </i>

46:39.660 --> 46:42.510
<i>♪ We stomp to rise you </i>

46:42.710 --> 46:45.380
<i>♪ Before you die </i>

46:45.580 --> 46:48.260
<i>♪ You scared of death,</i>
<i>though ♪</i>

46:48.460 --> 46:51.220
<i>♪ You'll ride together </i>

46:51.420 --> 46:53.480
<i>♪ Next time you see us </i>

46:53.680 --> 46:57.570
<i>♪ Be too late to cry </i>

46:57.770 --> 46:59.180
<i>Northside</i>

46:59.380 --> 47:02.520
<i>Skull and Bones Gang!</i>
<i>[cheering]</i>
